                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d545">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">393.1115/3416: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in China</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Johnson</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Hankow</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1938-07-19T11:00:00+08:00"
                            >July 19, 1938—11 a.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received July 19—7:30 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>361. Shanghai’s 1003, July 18, 6 p.m. regarding protection American nationals at
                    Kiukiang, Kuling and Nanchang. I have nothing to add to what I have already said
                    in my 347, July 11, 4 p.m., unless the Department has specific instructions for
                    me.</p>
                <p>Repeated to Shanghai. Shanghai please relay to Tokyo.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Johnson</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
